<p>Jagjit Singh co-founded Imperial Auto in 1969, and has been with the company for the past five decades. He started the company with low-pressure fuel assemblies for tractors and automotive vehicles in India, and over time expanded to include other products such as coolant hoses, rubber hoses, and nylon. Mr. Singh also played an instrumental role in entering joint venture partnerships such as Sumitomo Riko, Nichirin, and Martor. He currently holds an advisory role and continues to work towards the success of the organization.</p>
