<p>Viraj Sawhney joined the Imperial Auto board in 2022. Mr Sawhney is a Managing Director at Warburg Pincus and joined the investment firm in 2005. Prior to joining Warburg Pincus, Viraj was an Engagement Manager with McKinsey &amp; Company where he spent five years serving clients across India, S.E. Asia and Australia. Mr. Sawhney evaluates investment opportunities across TMT and business services. Sectors covered by him include logistics, telecom, technology services and BPO. He is a Director of Encora Holdings Limited (earlier known as Indecomm Corporation), Tide TopCo, Inc., Princeton Digital Group, Imperial Auto, Ecom Express, Rivigo and Stellar Value Chain Solutions. Mr. Sawhney holds a BA degree in Mathematics from St. Stephens College (Delhi University) and a Post-Graduate Diploma in Management from IIM Ahmedabad.</p>
